member.param:
This parameter specifies the device that is to be initialized (Resource Name). The syntax for this parameter is: TED4000(DFU): USB0::0x1313::0x8040::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR TED4000 : USB0::0x1313::0x8048::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR LDC4000(DFU): USB0::0x1313::0x8041::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR LDC4000 : USB0::0x1313::0x8049::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR ITC4000(DFU): USB0::0x1313::0x8042::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR ITC4000 : USB0::0x1313::0x804A::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR CLD1000(DFU): USB0::0x1313::0x8047::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR CLD1000 : USB0::0x1313::0x804F::DEVICE-SERIAL-NUMBER::INSTR
For remote VISA sessions use. VISA://HOSTNAME[:PORT]/ as a prefix. Where HOSTNAME is the name of the machine running the VISA server and PORT is the TCP port of the VISA server.
Note: You may use VISA <Find Resources> to get the Resource Name for your device. Use the search patterns below for <Find Resources>. TED4000: USB?*INSTR{VI_ATTR_MANF_ID==0x1313 && (VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x8040 || VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x8048)} LDC4000: USB?*INSTR{VI_ATTR_MANF_ID==0x1313 && (VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x8041 || VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x8049)} ITC4000: USB?*INSTR{VI_ATTR_MANF_ID==0x1313 && (VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x8042 || VI_ATTR_MODEL_CODE==0x804A)}
